## 1. Design Goals

- Make command entry points, argument rules, and execution results unambiguous
- Prioritize stable output, diagnosable failures, and exit codes that scripts can trust

## 2. System Boundary

- Inputs: command names, subcommands, flags, environment variables, config files
- Outputs: terminal text, machine-readable results, exit codes, optional file output
- External systems: local file systems, remote APIs, external commands, or credential systems
- Outside the system: graphical interfaces and long-running background services

