## 4. Module Design

| ID | Module | Responsibility | Requirements |
|---|---|---|---|
| `DES-001` | Command Parser | Parses command trees, flags, help output, and config entry points | `FR-001`, `FR-002` |
| `DES-002` | Executor and Output Formatter | Runs the core flow, formats output, and controls exit codes | `FR-001`, `FR-002` |

## 5. Data and State

- Core entities: parsed command context, resolved config, execution result, error objects
- Key fields: command name, flag values, config source, exit code, stdout content
- State transitions: parse input -> validate arguments -> execute command -> emit output -> return exit code

## 6. Interfaces and Contracts

| Interface | Input | Output | Failure modes | Requirements |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| `[CLI] tool <subcommand> --flag value` | flags, config, environment variables | stdout, stderr, exit code | invalid flags, missing config, dependency failure | `FR-001`, `FR-002` |

## 7. Technical Decisions and Trade-Offs

- Decision: separate command parsing, execution logic, and output formatting explicitly
- Alternatives: mix all logic directly in the command entry functions
- Why not chosen: argument validation, testing, and failure handling would become hard to control quickly

Record important decisions in `docs/adr/` when appropriate.

